MRs and they can't get in there edgewise.<P>If Verant wanted it to be a quest-component ONLY they should have made it no stats.<P>It irks me that people would begrudge someone a piece of equipment they might like just so SOMEONE ELSE can get a piece of equipment.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Euboa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ah, I take it back if you need the dragon books as a precursor for the Robe.  But if the Robe drops of the regular Lich then casters should go for it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Helamor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dragon books => Book of Scale => Miragul's Phlactery => Spawns Live Miragul => Drops Miragul head and robe.<P>Turn in the head AND the robe, plus Soulfire and Ghoulbane, and you get the Fiery Avenger.<P>So yes, any time you see someone running around in Miragul's robe, it cost a paladin a Fiery Avenger.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Valya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What Helamor said, except he left out the last step, turn in Fiery Avenger and Mark of Atonement (separate sub quest) to get Fiery Defender, the paladin epic. So any time a caster gets a Miragul robe it cost a paladin his or her epic.<P>On the plus side the robe step *can* be multiquested if the caster raises faction with the Deepwater Knights (one of the paladin guilds in Erudin), I know (through the paladin boards) of a necro who looted Miragul robe under a misunderstanding and raised their faction enough to multiquest with the paladin whose quest he inadvertantly de-railed.<P>I agree, its a shame verant made Miragul's robe with good stats, and I suppose there's some argument that int casters shoudl get to roll on the books for it (ugh)  but its *not* the best caster robe out there, while the Fiery Defender is the best paladin weapon (possibly barring some stuff from ToV).<p>[This message has been edited by Valya (edited 04-28-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Natosha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually he lead raids and wouldn't take a book until 2 dropped to loot a book.  If one dropped it went to a paladin.  If 2 dropped one went to him and the other to a paladin.  He also made it clear that this was going to happen before every raid, so if people didn't like it they had the option to leave.    </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alliliel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well the Necro on Tunare who has the Miragul robe didn't ninja it, he looted his own dragon books and everything to make it.<P>It seems someone above was under the impression some other person spawned Miragul. Not so here.<P>------------------<BR><B>Alliliel Archfalcon</B><BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR><A HREF="http://www.kriegeronline.com" TARGET=_blank>Krieger</A><BR>Tunare Server is my uber-guild</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Valya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I understand that according to the story, the guy who soloed nagafen now has a miragul robe.... that means he also got a vox book, did a couple intermediate steps, and spawned miragul, presumably he was able to assemble a raid of folks willing to kill miragul for him.  Well if he wants to go to the trouble of questing for the robe, there's certainly nothing to stop him. As a 57 paladin with no chance in hell of ever seeing a vox or nag book myself its just a bit disheartening to see something like that happen. :/</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
